('254829215', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Took a great app and made it unusable', 'I\'m on the road, and want to use Waze. I open it and first get a settings warning that Waze wants to access my location.  No kidding. But it\'s changed to a choice between \"never\" and \"always\" with no option for only when the app is open.  Okay I can live with that.  Then I get a soothing aqua screen that is \"downloading languages\" for eight minutes.  Then a failure message saying \"failed to install voice lines.\"  Huh?\n\nI thought maybe it was still trying to download using the hotel wifi so I shut off wifi and tried again.  Still no luck.  \n\nWaze was a simple very useful and effective app that is now useless.', '41622717', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Very nice, but ...', 'The idea and the implementation is in principle not bad done. But there are a few things that are very annoying: -if the data connection changes, e.g. From WiFi to LTE, then listen to Waze completely with the communication, there are no more updates. - if you want to use Waze on several devices, then you have to allow full access to contacts, etc., as soon as you want to log on to the second device. Why? Apart from that, I could not successfully log on to my existing Waze account on my iPad. - if you choose as an audio output &quot;BT-Telefongespräch&quot;, then this connection is established quite often (radio interrupts and switches to BT), but there is neither hinweison nor announcement.', 'Waze', 0.201356, 1, 0, 1, 1, '2017-03-24 13:19:42', 'all', 119, 0, -1, 0.875, 'ot', 'br'),
