('277906682', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Latest Version Unstable and Unreliable', 'Update 11/30/2016:\n\nA recent update (11/21) completely messed up the sound and the volume control. When the app is in the foreground, you can hardly hear it and the volume buttons adjust Ringer volume rather than speaker volume.  If you switch to any other app you can hear Waze but won\'t have the written directions. \n\nThe app is still unstable and throws in spurious directions from time to time.  \n\n------------- \n\nI have been using Waze for about 18 months and found it helpful in many situations. But after the latest updates it has become unreliable.  It keeps quitting and/or disconnecting from its server with no warning. When that happens it either goes silent (which is a clue that there\'s a problem) or starts spitting out nonsense instructions to make nonexistent turns on nonexistent streets.  \n\nI have also learned to treat many of its instructions with skepticism. Frequently it routes you through a labyrinth of little streets simply to avoid one traffic light that you would come to if you just stayed on the major street you were in, because the computer decided this would save 40 seconds.  Often it has the opposite effect, bringing you out at a challenging stop sign to turn left.  \n\nAnyway, be warned that this app is becoming more unstable with each update and you must keep a careful eye on it to make sure it has not shut down without warning.', '148377330', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Hammer', 'That is exactly what I was looking for: a navi that brings me fastest way through the major city traffic jam. Through the smallest streets, if necessary via parking lots. I am surprised to find out which way is the best today. I know myself really well, but Waze always finds surprising ways and trick 17 and 18. Also on routine stretches I do not go without without, the adjustment of the route and the warnings come in real time. Fortunately, traffic jams are also recorded in the smallest streets. Bad luck is when no Wazer was on the road. Absolutely this lovingly designed and daily delight-making app use. Since we have everything from. Waze is definitely the most useful, funniest, most playful and best working app on my iPhone. There are even more features, since no wishes remain open. Only you have to give yourself. Thanks to the developers!', 'Waze', 0.219237, 1, 1, 1, 1, '2017-03-24 13:33:16', 'all', 138, 0, 2, 0.75, 'br', 'ot'),
