('43514421', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Great Route finder, and directions, lousy map.', 'My big frustration with Waze is their incredibly stupid default map interface.  If you learned to read maps, oriented NSEW, North at the top, etc. then you will find WAZE map interface very much worse, especially if you are en route.  Don\'t bother trying to open it.  Use another map in that case.  \n\n(I found out how to fix the default map interface by enabling Lock-North-Up mode and disabling Auto-Zoom much better!) \n\nAlso on that same screen you can change Alert notifications, so go ahead and turn off the Shoulder Hazard Alert to stop hearing the \"Vehicle stopped on shoulder ahead\" alert.  You will add years to your life. \n\nIt\'s great at finding viable routes and fairly good at giving directions (sometimes the director gets cut off). \n\nIt\'s very bad when arriving at your destination. It will often say you\'ve arrived but then keep shouting directions at you.  I just terminate the app at the point.  \n\nStill it\'s probably one of the best free GPS you are going to find for alerts about your drive.', '203847084', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Top', 'Works very well! Since I have not heard about the last kilometers before home and drifted into a fat traffic jam - I never ride without it !!  However, there are still a few weaknesses: it is not enough to report in the app. You have to mark them online in the map and you need an appropriate map editor level. Luckily, there is the chat and you can ask people for help, which do the gladly.  The more you join, the better!', 'Waze', 0.214664, 1, 0, 1, 1, '2017-03-24 15:32:03', 'all', 245, -1, 0, 0.875, 'ot', 'ot'),
