('133672417', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Need a white UI', 'The app for music is fine; music is terrible these days anyways, but I like it in the background when I\'m working, running, driving, etc. UI is horrible because of the black background. I know I\'m not the only one who drives in sunny Southern California with shades on, and the dark UI makes it difficult and DANGEROUS to navigate while driving. I\'m not a person who texts and drive, but in horrendous SoCal traffic conditions, I would like to easily change my music selection when stopped at a light or moving slowly. I have to lift up my sunglasses every time so that I can see the screen. Spotify designers need to go back to design school and read up on design research and at least have the option of a white or light interface with high contrast. Even better, have an option to auto switch based on lighting conditions (like the light/dark modes of a navigation system). Please upgrade to 2016.', '284534857', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Really strong', 'There\'s (... with Premium) nothing to complain about! Top marks deserved. Surprisingly, however, The sound quality is by the mobile phone (Iphone) with good earphones again significantly better than with the HiFi surround system.', 'Spotify', 0.0829836, 0, 0, 1, 1, '2017-03-25 23:47:22', 'long', 383, -1, -1, 1, 'ot', 'ot'),
('134076296', 'applestore', 'United States', 'New version is terrible', 'I use this every day. Not for the traffic, but for the reporting of accidents and speed traps, and to contribute my speed info. I use it so often that I am at royalty level. Has saved us time on quite a few occasions by detouring around traffic on longer road trips.\n\nHowever... Version 4 brought a redesign and with it came bugs. Some buttons are now too small, and require more focus to tap while driving. Often I am given a map with not a single street name on it for miles. Also, now I can\'t report any road hazards or traffic conditions on the other side of the road. Accidents and cops still work, but any other report has no \"other side\" option. So stupid to have left that out. Also when reporting police you can\'t do other side AND hidden/visible. Could always do this in the old version.\n\nWhen waze brings back the ability to report things on the other side of the road, I will increase my rating. Until then, 1 star.', '153200652', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Makes almost fun', 'Use the app for a few days and am very impressed how up-to-date the messages are. My Navi is not there with ... unfortunately some of my own messages were not recorded, so I would like to send the app every day through a blocked street and every day I report the blocking again. Points are not yet recorded (maybe coming soon). The data consumption is really limited, but one is well advised to connect his mobile phone on the road with a power source.', 'Waze', 0.206553, 0, 0, 1, 1, '2017-03-25 23:48:47', 'long', 384, -2, 1, 0.625, 'ot', 'br'),
