('156919611', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Super useful, but could be better', 'Update 11-20-16\n\nWaze used to be great, but has really gone downhill since Google bought it. It\'s much less accurate at knowing where there are actually traffic problems, and recently has a tendency to route around totally non-existent obstacles. For example, it has taken me literally around the block back to the same place multiple times lately. It has taken me off the freeway onto surface way streets and back onto the freeway in the same place, or the next exit when there was absolutely nothing to avoid on the freeway. \n\nI used to love Waze, but it\'s useful is diminishing rapidly. \n\nOriginal pre-google review:\nI use Waze every day in LA because it\'s the only app that offers good off-freeway routing around traffic, but I also get frustrated with it every day. Because I know the city, I can usually ignore it and choose a different route when I know it\'s routing me to cross a really busy street with no signal or or something else I don\'t want to do. I know people who won\'t use it because of that one tendency. \n\nI agree with others that adding the street name earlier to turn cues, and announcing the next step immediately after a turn would be helpful. But it\'s way better than it used to be at giving advance cues, especially for multiple quick turns. \n\nThings I\'d like to see improved include:\n1. Make it easier to go back and forth from close up to overview and lock in overview mode, and quickly see overview in route options. \n2. Show traffic across the map more clearly (like Google)\n3. Have a setting to avoid \"suicide crossings\" with no signal\n4. Let you ask for more than 3 route options. \n5. Let you ask it to calculate  specific route options, eg. Long Beach to Santa Monica \"via 405, route 90 and Lincoln Blvd\"', '148377330', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Hammer', 'That is exactly what I was looking for: a navi that brings me fastest way through the major city traffic jam. Through the smallest streets, if necessary via parking lots. I am surprised to find out which way is the best today. I know myself really well, but Waze always finds surprising ways and trick 17 and 18. Also on routine stretches I do not go without without, the adjustment of the route and the warnings come in real time. Fortunately, traffic jams are also recorded in the smallest streets. Bad luck is when no Wazer was on the road. Absolutely this lovingly designed and daily delight-making app use. Since we have everything from. Waze is definitely the most useful, funniest, most playful and best working app on my iPhone. There are even more features, since no wishes remain open. Only you have to give yourself. Thanks to the developers!', 'Waze', 0.20838, 1, 1, 1, 1, '2017-03-26 00:41:06', 'long', 406, -1, 2, 0.625, 'ot', 'ot'),
('15737676', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Worthless', 'Yes very harsh title you\'ll see why I think this driving gps app needs to be retired or the algorithms need to be rewritten. Oh wait, better yet, use AI instead. Or a robot. Or a self driving car. The hyper loop. You get my point.  All this tech is great but needs A LOT of work.  The app doesn\'t do what it\'s supposed to do. I live in two of the worse traffic areas LA and the Bay Area. My commute is 40 miles each way can take 30 mins or 3 hrs. The rub is lately Waze thinks it\'s saving (a whole 2 mins) me time by changing my route (exiting freeway and driving on residual roads) when in actuality adds more commute time. The delay message pops up and up and up. Example, the route Waze suggested would get me home in hour 15. I followed the suggested route and I waited for 45 mins to get on a freeway. The entrance was 1000 feet away. Tons and tons of traffic. The app isn\'t improving driving it\'s making it worse. \n\nEveryone on the planet is using Waze and sending everyone on the same route. Defeats the propose of the app. It\'s become so mainstream and tons of users. The backend can\'t handle or manage the information the drivers are generating to recalculate a better route for others to follow. \n\nI know it\'s not Waze fault for the traffic. Traffic is part of driving in California. \n\nI the app is worthless for me to use. I\'ll stick to driving the crazy freeways of Northern and Southern California. If it\'s to nasty I\'ll find a nice bar to relax. BTW, I have deleted the app.', '41889820', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Do what you want', 'Very stable, perfect to plan the arrival time and communicate and share on many occasions. To see the current road situation also in the city center and to carry with the actuality of the data with is simply smart!', 'Waze', 0.208984, 0, 0, 1, 1, '2017-03-26 00:42:14', 'long', 407, 0, 0, 1, 'ot', 'ot'),
