('168231910', 'applestore', 'United States', 'I TRIED', 'I really tried to give Waze a chance. And by a TRIED I mean 7-8 months... but there was no way. It consistently took me \"around traffic\" which just ended up making my trips way longer than if I had just gone through traffic in the first place. It did that to me about 7-8 times before I pulled the plug.\nIt took me 2.5 miles OUT of my way just to cut across maaaybe 1 mile of traffic. \nI had just moved to a larger city and had no clue where anything was so I highly depended on this app. I found myself sitting in parking lots trying to find routes on my own because of how bogus some of the suggested routes were.\nOne part that I hated was it never actually let me know which routes included tolls and which didn\'t.\nObviously, as a newbie to a big city I would take the fastest route it suggested... low and behold! It was a toll road. \n\nAnyway, I\'m not necessarily a whiny, negative person. And this is actually my first ever app review after being an iPhone user for over 6 years, but I was just super disappointed.\nMy suggestion: focus less on the flashy, fun characters and more on the actual GPS/real time traffic update algorithm.', '148377330', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Hammer', 'That is exactly what I was looking for: a navi that brings me fastest way through the major city traffic jam. Through the smallest streets, if necessary via parking lots. I am surprised to find out which way is the best today. I know myself really well, but Waze always finds surprising ways and trick 17 and 18. Also on routine stretches I do not go without without, the adjustment of the route and the warnings come in real time. Fortunately, traffic jams are also recorded in the smallest streets. Bad luck is when no Wazer was on the road. Absolutely this lovingly designed and daily delight-making app use. Since we have everything from. Waze is definitely the most useful, funniest, most playful and best working app on my iPhone. There are even more features, since no wishes remain open. Only you have to give yourself. Thanks to the developers!', 'Waze', 0.258334, 1, 2, 1, 1, '2017-03-26 00:59:47', 'long', 417, -2, 2, 0.5, 'ot', 'ot'),
