('21915813', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Great option to a GPS', 'So the good: It\'s free, it\'s easy to set up, it\'s updated often so if you live in a city going through lots of construction, odds are if there are road closures Waze won\'t direct you down those roads. In fact, since users can send updates, those changes are almost real time.\n\nThis can also include detouring you in case of bad traffic, though if traffic had eased up on your original route the app may not be updated fast enough and still send you on a circuitous drive.\n\nThe maps appear clear, and even in vertical mode looks pretty good.\n\nThe bad: It\'s not \"free\". You still see ads, and of course if you tie the app in with social media you can be sure as hell your personal driving data and everything else is being sold to anyone with two bits in their pocket. Which brings up another issue that bothers me. Waze is ALWAYS running location services, even when you\'re not using the app. If you go to Privacy > Location Services in iOS, you only have options to deny the app or allow the app access. No choice for \"while using\". There\'s zero reason for Waze to know where I\'m going when I\'m not in need of a GPS.', '8518416', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Good scout', 'Quickly find good replacement routes for clogged roads', 'Waze', 0.0490264, 0, 1, 1, 1, '2017-03-26 14:01:48', 'long', 450, 1, 1, 1, 'ot', 'ot'),
