('25406216', 'applestore', 'United States', 'They RUINED Waze ?', 'UPDATE 2: \n\nMore updates, more annoyances. Lots more ads and a whole new level of annoying social networking: more is not better.  \n\nYes, Waze has gone the way of Alta Vista. Let\'s hope they course-correct soon!  I now put Waze in the category of \"dangerous to use for driving navigation\".  Where did the old Waze go???\n\nUPDATE: \n\nSometimes Waze does give me crazy directions.  I think Waze always tries to show me the fastest route, but sometimes that fastest route is only  2 seconds faster and consists of a whole lot of annoying turns through residential neighborhoods.\n\nI don\'t mind when alternate directions saves me minutes in \"high traffic\" situations, but it is annoying when a crazy route saves me 3 seconds.  I still find Waze to be a top-notch app.\n\nOriginal Review:\n\nI have to say that I am completely impressed by Waze.  It\'s smart.  It automatically tries to find the best route considering real-time traffic.  And in my experience it does a great job.  Today I was driving home and it picked a great alternative route - almost the same route I would have taken considering the time of day… except Waze\'s route was a bit better than mine.', '148377330', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Hammer', 'That is exactly what I was looking for: a navi that brings me fastest way through the major city traffic jam. Through the smallest streets, if necessary via parking lots. I am surprised to find out which way is the best today. I know myself really well, but Waze always finds surprising ways and trick 17 and 18. Also on routine stretches I do not go without without, the adjustment of the route and the warnings come in real time. Fortunately, traffic jams are also recorded in the smallest streets. Bad luck is when no Wazer was on the road. Absolutely this lovingly designed and daily delight-making app use. Since we have everything from. Waze is definitely the most useful, funniest, most playful and 