('285534619', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Bloated app its not as good as it ince was.', 'Cant stop for a second and look at the map when ads pop out of nowhere blocking the map. Also its a battery killer once you install this app say goodbye to your battery. Why does it want my location even when app not in use? Sounds fishy. Lets say I forgot to bring cash so I choose a route with no tolls the app will simply without telling me change the route. So whats the point of me choosing routes only to arrive at a toll booth and get fined for not having exact change. Its still the best gps app out there saved me from getting tickets since members do a great job of pointing out cops. But its not as good as it once was. Also now since google owns it you have to give them your phone number if you want to use a number of features. Really my phone number? For what? There is no need for that other than to identify me profile me and sell my behavior to third parties. If you are going to be selling my behavior at least get rid of the apps. \n\nGreat app terrible privacy and battery issues.', '8518416', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Good scout', 'Quickly find good replacement routes for clogged roads', 'Waze', 0.0496107, 0, 0, 1, 1, '2017-03-26 14:43:43', 'long', 493, -1, 1, 0.75, 'ot', 'ot'),
