('31249338', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Useful tool, but could be better', 'I generally like the Waze app, but some improvements could be made: 1) While I drive, I listen to the directions and alerts more than I look at the screen since I don\'t have a cradle or holder to keep it in sight. When I\'m stopped I like to give the screen a quick glance, but it is mostly obscured by annoying ads. So much for the quick glance, and a star. 2) I have to listen to music on my phone while using the app to hear the directions (listening through my phone is not effective enough). That in itself is not a problem. However, the volume of songs varies, meaning that sometimes I can barely hear directions unless the music is close to deafening. Likewise, sometimes I have to turn up my music quite a bit to hear it, which then results in a near-heart attack when the directions are given. It would be nice if the app volume would adjust itself to the volume of the song that\'s then playing; one less star. Fix those two things, and I\'ll bump it up to 5.', '41622717', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Very nice, but ...', 'The idea and the implementation is in principle not bad done. But there are a few things that are very annoying: -if the data connection changes, e.g. From WiFi to LTE, then listen to Waze completely with the communication, there are no more updates. - if you want to use Waze on several devices, then you have to allow full access to contacts, etc., as soon as you want to log on to the second device. Why? Apart from that, I could not successfully log on to my existing Waze account on my iPad. - if you choose as an audio output &quot;BT-Telefongespräch&quot;, then this connection is established quite often (radio interrupts and switches to BT), but there is neither hinweison nor announcement.', 'Waze', 0.223826, 1, 0, 1, 1, '2017-03-26 15:07:45', 'long', 513, -1, -1, 1, 'ot', 'br'),
