('49363530', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Lot of potential', 'Update:  11/24/16\n\nFew key irks of the app. \n\n1) No option to use location \'only when using the app.\' You can allow Waze to \"always\"  track you, or never track you.\n\n2) Turning off the wazetracker (putting it to sleep) is pretty buried and a pain tho access\n\n3) Apple Watch please.\n\nPROS:\n\n- very handy when there wazers near by to report situations.\n\n- bluetooth integration with car sound system, so directions are spoken through car speakers - big plus and makes the app like a built in system for the vehicle.\n\n- easy to contribute and report issues.\n\n- easy to enter addresses.\n\nCONS:\n\n- cant tell if reported traffic is north, south, east or west. So if you are traveling northbound you see a traffic jam but later discover traffic is south bound etc... Map detail isn\'t enough to illustrate which side if the road.\n\n- directions can be questionable, in that if you already know the roads you really question some of the long around about ways (not resulting from traffic re-routing).\n\n- ads - super annoying. Quite distracting and want them gone. Taco Bell... even if the Taco Bell hasn\'t existed for many years, you still get ads for ghost Taco Bell. No ads.\n\n- road closure tags are buggy and force direction to be selected, but the needed options do not exist.\n\n- privacy seems iffy... and how data is being used.\n\nNice to Haves:\n\n- better integration with contact book so you click the address already stored etc..rather than having to retype.\n\n- when viewing the the iPhone in landscape mode, large area of the top of screen used for directions, and large part of bottom screen used for trip details. Not much room to see the map after these overlays. Think there are opportunities to better design the info displays.\n\nBtw - please let me know if some of these options exist.. maybe a setting not tried etc.', '41622717', 'applestore', 'Germany', 'Very nice, but ...', 'The idea and the implementation is in principle not bad done. But there are a few things that are very annoying: -if the data connection changes, e.g. From WiFi to LTE, then listen to Waze completely with the communication, there are no more updates. - if you want to use Waze on several devices, then you have to allow full access to contacts, etc., as soon as you want to log on to the second device. Why? Apart from that, I could not successfully log on to my existing Waze account on my iPad. - if you choose as an audio output &quot;BT-Telefongespräch&quot;, then this connection is established quite often (radio interrupts and switches to BT), but there is neither hinweison nor announcement.', 'Waze', 0.229355, 1, 1, 1, 1, '2017-03-26 16:35:30', 'long', 614, -1, -1, 1, 'ot', 'br'),
